  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Trade Operations Specialist",
  "description": "<p>Salling Search is currently assisting an international trading company in the search for a <strong>Trade Operations Specialist</strong> based in Singapore.</p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Coordinate seaborne deliveries with Trading and Shipping teams.</li><li>Prepare import/export documentation per shipment and Letters of Credit requirements.</li><li>Communicate daily with suppliers, customers, shipping agents, banks, and surveyors to manage shipment documentation.</li><li>Ensure timely issuance of all cargo-related documents (10–15 per shipment).</li><li>Oversee shipment operations, including invoicing, documentation, LC presentation, and vendor payments.</li><li>Manage Import/Export Letters of Credit, collections, and banking transactions under international trade regulations.</li><li>Coordinate invoicing for incoming/outgoing shipments and provide accurate reporting.</li><li>Act as the main contact for internal and external stakeholders throughout the shipping process.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree in Logistics, International Trade, or related field.</li><li>1–3 years in international trade, import/export, shipping, or finance.</li><li>Knowledge of shipping docs, LCs, bank guarantees, and trade regulations (UCP 600, ISBP 745, Incoterms 2020).</li><li>Advanced English; Mandarin a plus.</li><li>ERP (JD Edwards) and Microsoft Office proficiency.</li><li>Detail-oriented, organized, analytical, and able to meet tight deadlines.</li></ul><p><br />Contact <strong>Ellaine Legaspi </strong>at ellaine@sallingsearch.com for more info or apply via our website.</p><p><strong>LEGASPI ELLAINE GOROSPE</strong><br />Ellaine Legaspi Gorospe<br />Reg No: R1220634<br />EA License No: 15S7671</p>",
